article.headline: Princeton 71, Dartmouth 43
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Douglas Davis scored 15 points and Princeton defeated Dartmouth 71-43 on Friday night. Patrick Saunders added 11 points for the Tigers (18-8, 9-3 Ivy League), who saw 12 of their players score. Princeton has won two games in a row after losing two straight. The Tigers jumped out to a huge lead, as a 3-pointer from Dan Mavraides made the score 24-7 with 9:43 to play in the first half. Princeton led 39-20 at halftime. In the first half, the Tigers shot 51.6 percent from the field (16-for-31), compared to only 30.4 percent for Dartmouth (7-for-23). An 8-0 run in the second half gave Princeton its largest lead at 61-29 with 8:50 remaining. R.J. Griffin paced the Big Green (5-22, 1-12) with nine points. Dartmouth has lost four games in a row and is winless on the road this season.
